The paper focuses on the security of IIoT devices and proposes the use of machine learning and big data analytics for analyzing and securing IoT technology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the utilization of machine learning models for intrusion detection, which falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories. The paper also involves network vulnerability analysis, which is related to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses a case study involving the design of an intrusion detection system, which falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
